I‚Äôm an intellectual mind orientated person so historically the relationship I‚Äôve had with my body has been fearful and wary. I was so happy living from the eyebrow up that any movement/physical practice was awkward, weird and terrifying. When I had the courage to try Yoga I religiously stuck to you but 4 years in my body was ready to move onto cardio (again the fear and terror came up). So I tried some workouts from Pamela Reif and MadFit and wow...the quality of space you hold Adriene and your guidance is very very different. I got the sweat I needed although it seems it‚Äôs coming at the expense of my relationship and rapport to my body and self. The obnoxious pop or dance music doesn‚Äôt seem to help (I often mute them to focus on my breath and quality of movement) and the one minute of one exercise is really too short - once I feel I‚Äôve got a hang of it and I‚Äôm enjoying the movement and breath and it‚Äôs over, onto the next one. Reif doesn‚Äôt explain how to do it healthily without injuring yourself so I rely on what you‚Äôve told me. You‚Äôre practically installed in my head at this point!! What I‚Äôm trying to say is that I missed you and I greatly appreciate you on YouTube and the language you use around getting fit and bodies. It‚Äôs truly unique ‚ô•Ô∏è‚ô•Ô∏è‚ô•Ô∏è

I think I just understood what going with the flow means. 
Sometimes we take our expectations, perspectives and definitions of certain things for granted so that we get hit by a wave when things turn out to be different.
Now, it occured to me that this is natural and that it can actually be profitable to learn - not only on our own but also from and with others.

How many times have I realised that I tensed because I wasn't content with how a situation went or how something is.
Yet, I don't have any influence on certain aspects and instead I found myself thinking that even if it didn't go as planned it will still lead to something great. 
Maybe even greater than expected.
Maybe it happened because I needed to find or learn something, to get stronger or maybe it happened because I was just not ready.

What I've learned is that everything happens for a reason and "everything is as it should be" (- as you said, Adriene).
Today, I still find myself stressing over things I can't control but now I am able to cut the loop by breathing in and out, smiling and telling myself what I really need to hear.
No feeding of that anxious, scared or aggressive inner voice but calming it and reassuring that something great can always happen with just a little more patience. 

A big part of this new mindset comes from you.
Adriene, you've had a huge influence on my life so far and I'm incredibly grateful for that.
However, a lot of things we have to learn and find out by ourselves.   
Yes, we learn from and with others as I said but we have to make our own experiences as well.
We have to go our own way while assisting and being assisted by others. 

Seems like I also got the "serving others" thing now üòÇüëè
